AcT III. SCENE 6. [V. 1.]

Chremes is startled by the sudden appearance of Sophrona, a servant of hisLemnian wife, from Demipho's house. He learns from her the death of her mistress and the marriage of Phanium to Antipho. At first he fails to identify his own daughter with Phormio’s ward, and thinks that his nephew like himself must have married two wives : but the confusion is soon removed and his joy is unbounded.
